        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 8:03PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 802 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles west of Bryson City, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fontana Lake and Great Smoky Mountains National Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
